Class ImageElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • handlers.ImageElement

  • public class ImageElement
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains all a the data values required to place an image on the screen at a specified x and y position, with a specified scale, and displays it at a specified time and for a specified duration.
    Version:
    1.2 (05.03.15)
    Author:

    • Constructor Detail

      • ImageElement

        public ImageElement(java.lang.String sourcefile,
            float xstart,
            float ystart,
            float scale,
            float duration,
            float starttime,
            float specifiedWidth)
        Constructor method for ImageElement object.
        Parameters:
        sourcefile - the filename of the image
        xstart - the horizontal position of the top-left of the image, relative to the resolution of the screen
        ystart - the vertical position of the top-left of the image, relative to the resolution of the screen
        scale - scalar factor which scales the image size (default 1)
        duration - the length of time that the image should be displayed on the screen
        starttime - the time the image should be first displayed on the screen
        specifiedWidths - the required width of the image which is used to scale the image, preserving the aspect ratio
